def series_to_supervised(data, n_in=1, n_out=1, dropnan=True):
    n_vars = 1 if type(data) is list else data.shape[1]
    df = DataFrame(data)
    cols = list()
    # input sequence (t-n, ... t-1)
    for i in range(n_in, 0, -1):
        #print("shift " + str(i))
        cols.append(df.shift(i))
    # forecast sequence (t, t+1, ... t+n)
    for i in range(0, n_out):
        #print("shift out " + str(i))
        cols.append(df.shift(-i))
    # put it all together
    agg = concat(cols, axis=1)
    # drop rows with NaN values
    if dropnan:
        agg.dropna(inplace=True)
    return agg.values

#split a univariate dataset into train/test sets
def train_test_split(data, n_test):
    return data[:-n_test, :], data[-n_test:, :]

# fit an xgboost model and make a one step prediction
def xgboost_forecast(train, testX):
    # transform list into array
    train = asarray(train)
    # split into input and output columns
    trainX, trainy = train[:, :-1], train[:, -1]
    # fit model
    model = XGBRegressor(objective='reg:squarederror', n_estimators=1000, max_depth=7, eta=0.1, subsample=0.7, colsample_bytree=0.8)
    model.fit(trainX, trainy)
    # make a one-step prediction
    yhat = model.predict(asarray([testX]))
    return yhat[0]

# walk-forward validation for univariate data
def walk_forward_prediction(data, n_predict, n_hours):
    predictions = []
    history = [x for x in data]
    # step over each time-step in the test set
    count = 0 
    for i in range(n_predict):
        start = time.time()
        #print(f'step {i} di {n_predict}')

        # fit an xgboost model and make a one step prediction
        if i%n_hours == 0:
            #print("Train shape")
            #print(len(history))
            start_fit = time.time()
            # model fit phase
            train = asarray(history)
            # split into input and output columns
            trainX, trainy = train[:, :-1], train[:, -1]
            # fit model
            model = XGBRegressor(objective='reg:squarederror', n_estimators=1000, max_depth=7, eta=0.1, subsample=0.7, colsample_bytree=0.8)
            model.fit(trainX, trainy) #, early_stopping_rounds=50
            #print(f'Durata {count} train: {time.time()-start_fit}')
            count += 1

        # make a one-step prediction
        yhat = model.predict(asarray([history[-1][1:]]))[0]
        # store forecast in list of predictions
        predictions.append(yhat)
        # add actual observation to history for the next loop
        last_row = np.append(history[-1][1:], asarray(yhat))
        history.append(last_row)
        #print(f'Durata step {i} di {n_predict}: {time.time()-start}')
        
    return history, predictions

def walk_forward_prediction_unique_train(data, n_predict):
    print("Unique train")
    predictions = []
    history = [x for x in data]

    history = asarray(history)
    # split into input and output columns
    print(history.shape)
    trainX, trainy = history[:, :-1], history[:, -1]
    # fit model
    model = XGBRegressor(objective='reg:squarederror', n_estimators=1000, max_depth=7, eta=0.1, subsample=0.7, colsample_bytree=0.8)
    model.fit(trainX, trainy)
    
    start = time.time()
    to_predict = history[-1][1:]
    for i in range(n_predict):
        start = time.time() 
        yhat = model.predict(asarray([to_predict]))
        to_predict = np.append(to_predict[1:], asarray(yhat))
        predictions.append(yhat)
    #print(f'Durata Inferenza: {time.time()-start}')
    
    return history, predictions

def main(data, n_in, k, test_mode = False, unique_train = True, n_hours = 1):
    # column selection q_t1
    if (test_mode):
        values = data['PRA'].values[:-k].reshape(-1,1)
    else:
        values = data['PRA'].values.reshape(-1,1)

    #print("Total data shape: ")
    #print(values.shape)
    
    # transform the time series data into supervised learning
    data = series_to_supervised(values, n_in = n_in)
    
    #print("Supervised Learning transformation shape: ")
    #print(data.shape)
    if unique_train:
        data_final, predictions = walk_forward_prediction_unique_train(data, k)
    else:
        data_final, predictions = walk_forward_prediction(data, k, n_hours)
    
    return pd.DataFrame(predictions, columns=['pra'])


def check_date(object_path, start, end):
    try:
        date = datetime.strptime(re.findall('\d{4}[^a-zA-Z0-9]\d{2}[^a-zA-Z0-9]\d{2}', object_path)[0])
        if date >= START_DATE and date <= END_DATE:
            return True
        return False
    except:
        print("No date found " + object_path)
        return False

def create_features(df, label=None):
    """
    Creates time series features from datetime index
    """
    df['date'] = df.index
    df['hour'] = df['date'].dt.hour
    df['dayofweek'] = df['date'].dt.dayofweek
    df['quarter'] = df['date'].dt.quarter
    df['month'] = df['date'].dt.month
    df['year'] = df['date'].dt.year
    df['dayofyear'] = df['date'].dt.dayofyear
    df['dayofmonth'] = df['date'].dt.day
    #df['weekofyear'] = df['date'].dt.weekofyear
    
    X = df[['hour','dayofweek','quarter','month','year',
           'dayofyear','dayofmonth']] #'weekofyear'
    if label:
        y = df[label].astype(float)
        return X, y
    return X
